<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1600 GMT, June 3 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI -- At least 15 militants and seven Indian security
men were killed in separate shoot-outs in Jammu and Kashmir since
Friday night, an official spokesman said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
According to the Press Trust of India, 10 militants and five
security men were killed in four separate encounters in various
places in Indian controlled Jammu and Kashmir. (India-Kashmir)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LAGOS -- Nigerian President Olusegun Obasanjo has announced a
major cabinet reshuffle for the first time since he came to power
last May, with three ministers resigned and nine swapped positions,
said local media Saturday. (Nigeria-Cabinet-Reshuffle)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TOKYO -- A strong earthquake measuring 5.8 on the open-ended
Richter scale jolted eastern Japan on Saturday afternoon, the
Meteorological Agency said.
</P>
<P>
There were no immediate reports of casualties or damage and no
tsunami or tidal wave warning was issued. The epicenter of the
quake, which occurred at 5.54 p.m. local time (0854 GMT), was
estimated to be about 50 kilometers underground in the
northeastern part of Chiba Prefecture, east of Tokyo, the agency
said. (Japan-Earthquake)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
NAIROBI -- The Ethiopian forces launched an all-out attack on
the new Assab front at 3.30 a.m. (0130 GMT) Saturday, Eritrean
Foreign Affairs Ministry said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
"The Eritrean frontline at Assab is a new frontline set at 37
kilometers west of the Red Sea port city and the original
frontline was at Burrie, 71 kilometers from the port city," the
statement said. (Kenya-Ethiopia-Eritrea)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
COLOMBO -- Sri Lanka has sent another 4,000 soldiers to defend
the northern Jaffna peninsula where some 30,000 troops have been
battling separatist Tamil Tiger rebels, said Saturday Deputy
Minister of Defense General Anuruddha Ratwatte.
</P>
<P>
The military situation in Jaffna was still critical, Ratwatte
said. But with an improvement in troop morale, reinforcements and
new weapons, they were able to defend Jaffna. (Sri Lanka-
Reinforcements) 
</P>
</TEXT>
