<DOCNO> XIE20000604.0012 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Eritrea Claims Killing Over 3,700 Ethiopian Soldiers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Eritrea claimed on Sunday that some
3,755 Ethiopian troops were killed, wounded or captured by its
army on the Assab front and several heavy armored vehicles were
destroyed , according to a news release issued by the Eritrean
Foreign Ministry available here.
</P>
<P>
It said the Eritrean army have captured a large number of
medium and small arms, and communication radios in the battle. It
added that Eritrea has foiled the Ethiopian attacks which launched
on early Saturday morning on the Assab front.
</P>
<P>
The Assab front was quiet Sunday apart from intermittent
shelling that started around 10:00 a.m., the Eritrean foreign
ministry said.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia declared on May 31 that the war was over. The
announcement was made while it claimed to have recovered all
occupied territories from Eritrea, and attained all its military
objects.
</P>
<P>
The two countries are now involved in a new round of proximity
talks brokered by the Organization of African Unity (OAU) in
Algeria.
</P>
<P>
The latest round of fighting between the two Horn of Africa
neighbors erupted on May 12. The conflict between the two
countries started about two years ago, which left thousands of
people dead or wounded. 
</P>
</TEXT>
