<HEADLINE> Arab Committee to Finalize Plan for Regular Arab Summit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, June 4 (Xinhua) -- A five-member committee of the Arab
League will finalize a mechanism for the convocation of Arab summit
meeting on a regular basis, the league spokesman, Talaat Hamad,
said Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The foreign ministers of the committee members -- Egypt, Oman,
Syria, Tunisia and Yemen -- and Arab League Secretary General Esmat

Abdel Meguid will meet in Cairo on Tuesday to put the final touches
to the plan, Hamad told reporters.
</P>
<P>
The plan to be worked out by the committee will be submitted to
the 114th session of the Foreign Ministers Council of the Arab
League in Cairo on September 2, Hamad said.
</P>
<P>
The council will decide whether the league's charter will
include the proposal on holding an Arab summit each year, he added.
</P>
<P>
Under the draft plan, Arab leaders will meet in March to discuss
and coordinate stances on key political, economic and security
issues related to the Arab nation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
