<HEADLINE> Chinese Divers Shine at Hong Kong Diving Meet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Powerhouse China collected two
more titles on Sunday to bring their gold medal tally to five on
the final day of the Hong Kong Diving Meet.
</P>
<P>
"Our divers did not meet any resistance in this tournament, so
they performed well, " said Chinese teamleader Zhou Jihong, who
won a gold medal in Los Angles Olympics in 1984.
</P>
<P>
Zhou said :"When they go to the Sydney Olympics, steadiness and
psychology will be the keys to win golds."
</P>
<P>
The women's 10-meter platform turned out to be the showcase of
three Chinese divers.
</P>
<P>
Li Na, China's number one platform diver, outclassed her
teammate and arch-rivals Cai Yuyan and Sang Xu to defend her title
in the women's 10-meter platform with 614.52 points.
</P>
<P>
Li Na won the event last year.
</P>
<P>
Cai Yuyan and Sang Xu ranked second and third with 608.73
points and 584.76 points respectively.
</P>
<P>
In the men's three-meter springboard, China's Xiao Hailiang,
though lower in difficult difference than others, showed a steady
performance and led all the way by winning the event with 776.19
points.
</P>
<P>
Robert Newbery from Australia finished second with 723.39
points, followed by his compatriot Dean Pullar who got 663.21
points.
</P>
<P>
The three-day meet is one of the 14-leg FINA diving grand prix
series this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
