<HEADLINE> Chinese Environment News: Weekly Highlights (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Chinese capital Beijing has launched a massive campaign to
increase its residents' awareness of biodiversity and harmonious
co-existence of mankind and nature.
</P>
<P>
The city's leading parks and gardens have organized 40
activities and tens of thousands of Beijing residents took part in
such activities.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai Faces Difficult Flood Prevention Task
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai Municipal Flood Control Headquarters urged
related departments to pay much attention to flood prevention and
control measures.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai will see more rainfall than usual and be affected by
two or three typhoons during the coming flood season, the
headquarters warned.
</P>
<P>
Bad weather such as cyclones and hailstorms are also forecast
for the area by the city's observatory.
</P>
