<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thailand Holds 3rd Round of Senate Election </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, June 4 (Xinhua) -- The third round of Thailand's
senate election for the last 12-vacant Senate seats was held
Sunday, mostly in the northeastern provinces.
</P>
<P>
There were signs of possible vote buying and frauds in some
provinces during Sunday's voting, according to a report from
Thailand's Election Commission.
</P>
<P>
The commission said in the report that it has tentatively set
the date for the fourth-round poll on June 18, just one week
before the reconvention of the House of Representatives.
</P>
<P>
The ordinary elections for Thailand's 200 Senate seats were
held on March 4, but 78 winners were judged to have links with
polling fraud. The second round of election to fill those seats
was held on April 29, but was again marred by frauds.
</P>
<P>
The senatorial election is part of the country's political
reform plan based on the present constitution, aimed to eliminate
vote buying and frauds.
</P>
<P>
The 200-seat Senate will have the rights to examine and deprive
politicians who are found guilty of any irregular practice.
</P>
</TEXT>
