<HEADLINE> China to Offer Daily Air Quality Reports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Starting tomorrow, China will
release a daily report on the air quality in 41 major Chinese
cities, according to the China Environmental Monitoring Center.
</P>
<P>
Zhu Jianping, an expert with the center which will produce the
report, said today the cities include 32 provincial and autonomous
regional capitals and nine major coastal cities.
</P>
<P>
Six other major coastal cities will be added to the report
after the necessary monitoring equipment is installed, the sources
said.
</P>
<P>
The center currently produces a weekly report on the quality
of the air in 47 major cities on the Chinese mainland.
</P>
<P>
The daily service is expected to help improve people's
awareness about air pollution and other environmental issues, and
involve them in efforts to clean up the environment, Zhu said.
</P>
<P>
About a dozen leading cities, including Beijing and Tianjin,
already issue daily air quality announcements.  
</P>
