<HEADLINE> Foreigners Charged Same As Chinese for Medical Treatment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Foreigners in southwest China's
Chongqing Municipality are now paying the same fees for hospital
services as local citizens.
</P>
<P>
Li Xianglong, director of the city's public health bureau, said
the new regulation, which went into effect on June 3, was issued
to encourage more foreigners to invest in the city.
</P>
<P>
The new regulation put an end to the high medical charges for
foreigners, which were usually five times the fees paid by local
people.
</P>
<P>
The city has also selected several local hospitals with quality
medical services and a better environment as the first group to
provide foreigners with medical care. These hospitals are also
required to employ bilingual doctors, able to speak English or
Japanese, to better accommodate foreign patients. 
</P>
