<HEADLINE> Carlson Hospitality Targets Asia-Pacific for Market Expansion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Carlson Hospitality Worldwide,
one of the world's largest hospitality companies, announced here
Sunday that it is aggressively targeting Asia-Pacific for
continuing strategic expansion of its three hotel brands and
cruise ship itineraries in the region.
</P>
<P>
"As the Asian economy continues to rebound, the power of
branding and global marketing will play an increasingly important
role in the Asian hospitality industry of the new millennium,"
said Curtis Nelson, president and CEO of Carlson Hospitality
Worldwide at its annual business meeting that opened here Sunday.
</P>
<P>
"We expect an accelerating growth of our hotel brands and
cruise operations in Asia because of this important trend," he
added.
</P>
<P>
Carlson's three hotel brands, Regent International Hotels,
Radisson Hotels &AMP; Resorts and Country Inns &AMP; Suites By Carlson,
currently have a total of 39 hotels open in the Asia-Pacific
region, with a value of 1.6 billion U.S. dollars, and plans to
expand the company's total locations in Asia-Pacific to 55 by the
year 2001. 
</P>
