<HEADLINE> Popular Science Books Published in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 4 (Xinhua) -- The first two groups of books in a
popular science series written by academicians from the Chinese
Academy of Sciences (CAS) and the Chinese Academy of Engineering (
CAE) have been published.
</P>
<P>
In his preface for the series, President Jiang Zemin wrote that
publishing high-quality popular science books is vital for
promoting science and education in the country, and will help
improve the nation's grasp on science.
</P>
<P>
The just-published volumes include 50 books written by some
prominent scientists such as Nobel Prize Winner T.D. Lee, the late
Chinese scientist Wang Ganchang, and CAS vice-president Bai Chunli.
</P>
<P>
At today's news conference for the books' release, Lu Yongxiang,
president of the Chinese Academy of Sciences, said that science
popularization is crucial for the country's invigoration.
</P>
<P>
The series focuses on the most advanced theories as well as the
hot issues related to economic construction and social development,
Lu added.
</P>
<P>
Work on the books was started by the CAS and CAE scholars in
1998.
</P>
<P>
The completed series will include 175 books written by 176
scientists from the two academies.  
</P>
</TEXT>
