<HEADLINE> Bomb Blast in Southern Philippines Kills one </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 4 (Xinhua) -- A powerful bomb planted at a bus
terminal in Iligan City, the southern Philippines, exploded early
Sunday, killing one and seriously wounding four others.
</P>
<P>
Nilo Abagan, 52, a resident of the city was killed in the
explosion and his body has been dismembered by the blast, reports
from Iligan City said.
</P>
<P>
Four other civilians, two of them taxi drivers, were also hurt
in the incident, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
The victim was reportedly passing by the Super 5 Transit
terminal in the city when the bomb, tucked behind one of the bus
station's posts, went off at around 03:00 (19:00 GMT Saturday),
the reports said.
</P>
<P>
Earlier in the day, a bomb exploded at the Nino Aquino
International Airport in Manila, but no one was killed.
</P>
<P>
The Philippine government has blamed Muslim rebels for a spate
of bombings in Manila and the southern part of the country in the
past weeks. However, no rebel groups have claimed responsibility
for the incidents. 
</P>
