<HEADLINE> China Scores Third Straight Win in Pacific Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, June 4 (Xinhua) -- China defeated Japan two goals
against nil to remain unbeaten in the Pacific Cup women's soccer
tournament in Sydney on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
In other games, the United States defeated New Zealand 5-0 as
Cindy Parlow savored her second hat-trick performance and Canada
upset Australia 2-0.
</P>
<P>
By scoring goals either side of halftime, China won the opener
of the day to keep its clean slate as Bai Jie netted in the 41st
minute and Shui Qingxai added the second six minutes later.
</P>
<P>
In the curtain-raiser of the tournament, China defeated the
United States 1-0 and edged over Australia 5-4 on a penalty shoot-
out after both sides tied for a 1-1 deadlock after the two extra-
time periods.
</P>
<P>
Parlow, who scored three goals in Friday's 9-1 mauling of
Canada, started another goal-scoring spree late in the first half
with a powerful right-foot drive, and added two goals within three
minutes in the second period.
</P>
<P>
Thus, Parlow, 22, leads the tournament scorers' standings with
six goals from three games.
</P>
<P>
Christie Welsh scored the first two goals in the 11th and 29th
minutes for the Americans who started the tournament with a 0-1
loss to China in Canberra.
</P>
<P>
In the later game Sunday, Christine Sinclair scored in the 32nd
minute and Silvana Burtini found the net in the 43rd minute as
Canada held its 2-0 halftime lead till the final whistle.
</P>
<P>
In the round-robin six-nation tournament, China leads the
standings with nine points, followed by the U.S. and Canada on six
points, Australia and Japan on three points and New Zealand is yet
to register a point. 
</P>
</TEXT>
