<HEADLINE> Fresh Fighting Kills 14 Rebels in Northern Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Fresh fighting which erupted
between Sri Lankan troops and Tamil Tiger rebels has killed 14
rebels in the northern Jaffna peninsula where fighting has eased
after a few weeks' fierce battles, the government said Sunday.
</P>
<P>
A government statement said that government troops in ambush at
Karadiyankadu on Saturday engaged a group of eight rebels with
claymore mines and small arms fire as well as artillery and mortar
fire.
</P>
<P>
All eight rebels of Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE)
were killed, said the statement, adding that while withdrawing
troops attacked a rebel bunker and killed three rebels.
</P>
<P>
The statement said a fighting patrol operating ahead of the
defenses in Vempotukerni observed a rebel movement and engaged
them with small arms fire, killing three rebels.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE rebels, fighting for a separate state for minority
Tamils in Sri Lanka's north and east since 1983, have engaged in a
ferocious assault in recent weeks in a bid to retake their former
stronghold of Jaffna.
</P>
<P>
Deputy Minister of Defense General Anuruddha Ratwatte said
Saturday that the military situation in Jaffna was still critical,
but with an improvement in troop morale, reinforcements and new
weapons, they were able to defend Jaffna. 
</P>
</TEXT>
