<HEADLINE> Bomb Blast Rocks Afghan Capital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 4 (Xinhua) - A bomb blew off in central Kabul
early Sunday but fortunately no casualties or damage was caused,
sources from the Afghan capital said.
</P>
<P>
The bomb was planted at a corner of the Zarnigar Park, opposite
the ministry of communications building, and exploded during the
morning rush hour, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
Soldiers of the ruling Taliban militia cordoned off the area,
and said they would not rule out the possibility of a bigger blast
following the small explosion.
</P>
<P>
They suspected that it was supporters of opposition commander
Ahmad Shah Masood who had staged the explosion.
</P>
<P>
The Taliban seized Kabul in 1996 and now control most of
Afghanistan. Masood's forces in the northeast, however, have so
far foiled the militia's attempts to take the whole country.
</P>
