<DOCNO> XIE20000604.0123 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Paraguay Beats Ecuador in World Cup Qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Hugo Brizuela scored twice as
Paraguay downed Ecuador 3-1 at home in Asuncion Saturday night in
a 2002 World Cup third round qualifier in South America.
</P>
<P>
Delio Toledo opened the scoring for Paraguay in the 10th minute
before Brizula scored in the 42nd and 63rd minutes. Ecuador's
Ariel Graziani scored on a header in the 85th minute.
</P>
<P>
Ecuador, who lost to Brazil 4-3 earlier, resorted to a
defensive strategy against Paraguay by fielding only one foward.
</P>
<P>
And the victory was Paraguay's second of the tournament after a
1-0 win over Uruguay despite the absence of standout striker Roque
Santa Cruz who was nursing injuries at his German club Bayern
Munich. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000604.0124 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Weekly Review of Regional News In China (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI: Shanghai opened its largest website: www.eastday.com
on May 28. The website has 11,000 registered users and offers
information such as news, finance and economy, sports, life, photo,
forum and culture.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai reported a foreign trade turnover of 2.755 billion U.S.
dollars with the European Union (EU) during the first four months
this year, surging 62.5 percent from the same 1999 period.
</P>
<P>
TIBET: The average life expectancy in southwest China's Tibet
Autonomous Region has increased to 67 from 36 in the early 1950s.
Tibet's population has also increased from 1.15 million in 1952 to
2.55 million.
</P>
<P>
Tibet Autonomous Region issued a specific regulation for the
administration of its border areas, which went officially into
effect as of June 1. Tibet has a border line of more than 4,000
kilometers accounting for one fifth of China's total. The region's
border area makes up 25.8 percent of its territory.
</P>
<P>
Chinese scientists recently said research achievements have
shown that the original form of the insects in southwest China's
Tibet came from Eurasia and India. The Qinghai-Tibet Plateau
emerged out of sea in the late period of the Cenozoic Era, when
most of the insects had already come into being. So it is most
likely that the insects in Tibet came from neighboring Eurasia and
India.
</P>
<P>
SHAANXI: A serious traffic accident on May 28 in northwest
Shaanxi Province has left 26 dead and 19 others injured. A bus
carrying 45 passengers fell down a 30-meter-high cliff as it was
turning around.
</P>
<P>
YUNNAN: An international floral festival is to be held in
Kunming, capital of southwest China's Yunnan Province, from
September 28 to October 3. It is a grand international
horticultural event following the '99 Kunming Horticulture Expo in
the province.
</P>
<P>
Yunnan Province, located on Yunnan-Guizhou Plateau, will be
turned into the largest flower production and export base both in
China and Asia, said Huang Bingsheng, deputy governor of Yunnan
Province recently. Yunnan is well known as "kingdom of plants", "
garden of nature" and "botanical genes bank."
</P>
<P>
China will hold the first Ethnic Fashion Show in mid-July in
Kunming, capital of Yunnan Province. More than 2,000 items of
clothing from various ethnic groups in China will be displayed at
the show, including a 600,000-yuan Tibetan costume and a garment
made from fish skin.
</P>
<P>
LIAONING: A celebration was held on June 1 in Shenyang, capital
of northeast China's Liaoning Province, marking the 99th birthday
of General Zhang Xueliang, a national hero of modern China. Zhang
Xueliang, born on June 3, 1901 on a horse-drawn carriage in
northeast China's Liaoning Province, is now living in Hawaii in
the United States with his wife Zhao Yidi. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000604.0125 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Weekly Review of Regional News In China (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING: The Bank of China (BOC) has raised deposit and lending
rates for four major foreign currencies -- U.S. dollar, British
pound, euro and HK dollar, as well as the deposit rates for
Canadian dollar and Swiss franc in China.
</P>
<P>
China's first encyclopedia featuring the progress made by the
country in resource sciences over the past five decades was
published recently. The two-volume publication covers 19 subjects
related to resource sciences.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Water Resources predicts that floods may occur
in the Yangtze River Valley this summer. This forecast is based on
the fact that more rain is expected on the upper reaches of the
Yangtze and the Hanjiang river valleys, especially during the rain
season, which begins on June 16 on the Chinese lunar calendar.
</P>
<P>
Beijing has started a project to prolong the Chang'an Street,
key avenue in the capital. When the project completes at the end
of this year, the street will be extended from present 13
kilometers to 45 km. Chang'an Street is the thoroughfare along
which Tiananmen, Forbidden City and Zhongnanhai, site of the
Central Government, are located. And it serves as the venue of
many important political and diplomatic events.
</P>
<P>
Jin Deqing, former vice chairman of the board of directors at
the China International Trust and Investment Corporation (CITIC)
and chairman of the directors' board of the CITIC Ka Wah Bank, was
sentenced to life imprisonment for grafting public funds.
</P>
<P>
Drought in central China has been alleviated since May 29
thanks to heavy rains. However, drought continues to plague north
China. Statistics show that a total of 10 million ha of field have
been hit by drought, and 17.7 million people and 14.9 million
cattle do not have enough drinking water.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
