<HEADLINE> Pakistan Sends India Home in Asia Cup Cricket </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan dumped India out of the
seventh Asia Cup with a 44-run victory on Saturday to set up a
final clash against defending champions Sri Lanka on June 7, the
Independent newspaper reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan and Sri Lanka will meet Monday in the last league
match which only has academic interest after India bowed out of
the four-nation meet.
</P>
<P>
The defeat also dented India's remarkable record of reaching
all Asia Cup finals, except in 1986 when they did not take part in
the meet.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan batsman Yousuf Youhana, who reached the magical three-
fugure in the match, won the prize of man-of-the-match. 
