<HEADLINE> Indian Inflation Dips to 6.3 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 4 (Xinhua) -- India's inflation rate dipped
marginally by 0.08 percentage points to 6.3 percent for the week
ended May 20, despite a small rise in overall wholesale price
index during the week, an official release said here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The country's inflation rate touched a 74-week high of 6.38
percent during the week ended May 13, mainly on account of a
sustained increase in the prices of items under Fuel, Power, Light
&AMP; Lubricants.
</P>
<P>
The inflation rate for the week ended May 20 last year was
merely 3.33 percent.
</P>
<P>
During the week ended May 20, the wholesale price index for all
commodities increased by 0.1 percent to 151.9 as compared to 151.7
in the previous week, the official release said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
