quipped with the naval combat craft promised by Israel to crush
Sea Tigers, the naval unit of Tamil Tiger rebels, the official
Sunday Observer reported.
</P>
<P>
"Israel has agreed to supply Sri Lanka navy with these craft
which have the capacity to bombard shore targets from off-shore,"
said the newspaper.
</P>
<P>
It said the combat craft can launch missiles from different
kinds of sea platforms with a maximum range of 36 kilometers.
</P>
<P>
The strengthening of the navy's strike capability follows a
decision by military planners to neutralize the naval bases of
separatist rebels of Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE).
</P>
<P>
The LTTE rebels, fighting for a separate state for minority
Tamils since 1983, have engaged in a ferocious assault in recent
weeks in a bid to retake their former stronghold of Jaffna.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE naval bases are also known to be the principal landing
points for much of the rebels' clandestine supply deliveries by
sea.
</P>
<P>
"The new strategy will be to squeeze the LTTE's vital ordnance
supply lines by striking at the Sea Tiger bases and clandestine
harbors," said the paper.
</P>
<P>
It said military planners hope to neutralize the known Sea
Tiger strongpoints particularly along the eastern coastline from
Mullaitivu to Alampil and in the Challai sector.
</P>
<P>
Over the years Israel has supplied Sri Lanka navy with some
Dvora fast attack craft. The navy plans to provide computer guided
weapons systems for its whole fleet of Dvora craft. 
</P>
</TEXT>
