<HEADLINE> Albania Introduces 3-Year Budget System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Albania will follow a new three-year
budget system instead of the current annual one, Albanian
newspaper Voice of the People said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The new budget from 2000 through 2003, announced Friday by the
Albanian government, has drawn on the experience from developed
countries and got the support from World Bank, the newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
According to the new budget, the annual economic growth will be
8 percent, the state investment in 2003 will be five times that in
1996, and the budget revenue in 2003 will be 55 billion lekes (37.
9 million U.S. dollars) higher than that of 2000.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the budget envisages tax cuts, more foreign
investment and a 10 percent annual increase in both wage and
pension. 
</P>
</TEXT>
