<P>
LONDON -- Britain's Queen Elizabeth II met her son Prince
Charles' long-time companion Camilla Parker Bowles formally for
the first time at a party this week, the BBC reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The meeting took place at a 60th birthday party for King
Constantine, the former king of Greece, at the prince's home at
Highgrove in Gloucestershire. (Britain-Queen)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LONDON -- Britain will withdraw about 500 soldiers from
Northern Ireland due to improving security, thus reducing its
troop levels in Northern Ireland to the lowest point since 1970.
</P>
<P>
Northern Ireland's police head Ronnie Flanagan announced
Saturday that a battalion of troops based in middle Northern
Ireland are to return to England as part of an overall
demilitarization program. The soldiers will return home in two
weeks' time when their current six-month tour of Northern Ireland
ends. (N.Ireland-Troops)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LONDON -- Sinn Fein's chief negotiator Martin McGuinness
Saturday warned dissident republicans not to start attacking the
British mainland following the Hammersmith Bridge bombing.
</P>
<P>
The education minister in Northern Ireland's newly reinstated
power-sharing executive also condemned the bombers who damaged the
west London bridge Thursday. (N.Ireland-Sinn Fein) 
</P>
</TEXT>
