<HEADLINE> Uruguay Beats Chile 2-1 in World Cup Qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Dario Silva and Paolo Montero
each scored a goal to give Uruguay a 2-1 over Chile here on
Saturday in the third round of World Cup qualifying in South
America.
</P>
<P>
Silva put the host 1-0 ahead when he scored in the 35th minute
and Montero added the second six minutes later to give Uruguay
three badly need points in their quest for a spot in the 2002
World Cup.
</P>
<P>
The victory gave Uruguay six points in the tourney after three
games while the winless Chile has one. 
</P>
</TEXT>
