<HEADLINE> River Protection Drive to Have Official Website </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HOHHOT, June 4 (Xinhua) -- The official website of a major
river protection drive is now being created, and is scheduled for
completion this year as part of the effort to provide more
information via the Internet.
</P>
<P>
The website will mainly consist of information on the
development of river protection and how and where donations have
been used.
</P>
<P>
Last year, a project began to protect China's major rivers,
called "mother rivers," with a series of public activities to
arouse people's awareness of efforts to increase the forest
coverage rate and maintain the natural balance.
</P>
<P>
The protection drive mostly depends on people's donations, and
to date it has received 30 million yuan (3.6 million US dollars),
and afforestation accomplished with the use of these funds has
effectively covered 18,000 hectares of land. 
</P>
</TEXT>
