<HEADLINE> What's on Weekly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 4 (Xinhua) -- This week's concerts will start
with Stairway to Music 2000 Afternoon Concerts -- Jazz Series by
the Touchstone Jazz Quartet today at 14:00 at the Beijing Concert
Hall.
</P>
<P>
The Forbidden City Concert Hall will put on stage a Rainbow
Choral Series concert featuring Chinese lieder from the early 20th
century.
</P>
<P>
Concert-goers will be able to enjoy listening to some love
songs by the China Opera and Ballet Orchestra on Friday at the
Forbidden City Concert Hall. Songs will include selected music
from the movies of Titanic and Love Story, and old love lyric sung
by Carpenters.
</P>
<P>
This week's concerts will end with Stairway to Music 2000
Afternoon Concerts again. The Young People's Philharmonic of the
Beijing Musicians' Society will play some children's songs once
popular in the 1950s-60s and 1980s. 
