<HEADLINE> UAE's Non-oil Foreign Trade up 3.6 Percent in 1999 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, June 3 (Xinhua) -- The United Arab Emirates's non-oil
foreign trade had been growing in 1999, with the volume totaling
130.5 billion dirhams (35.66 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The growth rate was recorded at 3.6 percent, said a report
released by the UAE'S Industry Bank on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The report said the total import of the non-oil foreign trade
amounted to 98.5 billion dirhams (26.91 billion dollars) last year,
up 9 percent from 1998, while the export was down 10 percent to
reach 9 billion dirhams (2.46 billion dollars).
</P>
<P>
The entrepot trade was valued at 23 billion dirhams (6.28
billion dollars).
</P>
<P>
The figures also indicated that the non-oil foreign trade volume
of the UAE, the regional non-oil trade centre, has increased 166
percent since 1989, with the entrepot trade grown 147 percent at
the same time. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
