<HEADLINE> Great Earthquake Recorded off Sumatra; Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The quake was measured at magnitude 7.9 and occurred at 11:28 p.
m. local time, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The shock was felt strongly at Benjkulu, 70 miles north-
northeast of the epicenter, where it could have caused major
structural damages. It also was felt as far away as Jakarta, the
capital, 335 miles north-northwest of the center.
</P>
<P>
Eleven minutes after the original shock, an aftershock was
recorded at magnitude 6.7, the report said. 
</P>
